By CHIDINMA EWUNONU-ALUKO IBADAN- An Iyaganku Magistrates’ Court in Ibadan, on Wednesday sentenced a 23-year-old man, Isaac Dumabara to one month imprisonment for stealing one pot of stew and meat worth N40, 000 from a restaurant.Magistrate S. A Adesina, who found Dumabara guilty of theft, sentenced him without an option of fine.Earlier, the Police Prosecutor,  ASP Sikiru Ibrahim, told the court that Damubara also stole three gas cylinders, stabilizer and a pair of Adidas shoe from Pleasure Summit Restaurant, Magara Road, Iyaganku, Ibadan.Ibrahim further told the court that the convict also stole a 42-inche television worth N200, 000.He said the offence contravened the provisions of Section 390(9) of the Criminal laws of Oyo State. (NAN) By CHIDINMA EWUNONU-ALUKOIbadan- One Gbenga Odeniran, 46, was on Thursday docked in an Iyaganku, Magistrates’ Court, Ibadan for allegedly receiving a stolen vehicle worth N2.5 million.Odeniran, whose residential address was not provided, was charged with receiving suspected stolen property.The Prosecutor, Insp Sikiru Ibrahim told the court that the defendant allegedly… In "Metro" Ibadan - An Iyaganku Chief Magistrates’ Court, Ibadan, on Tuesday sentenced one Akeem Adeyemi, 31, to five months in prison for stealing inside a mosque during prayers to end the day's Ramadan fast. Adeyemi, whose address is unknown, had on Monday pleaded guilty to a two-count charge of felony and… In "News" Ibadan  -  A 21-year old man, Olakunle Olowoyeye, was on Wednesday dragged before an Iyaganku Chief Magistrates’ court in Ibadan for allegedly stealing cellphones and a digital pen at the University of Ibadan Central Mosque. Olowoyeye is facing a two-count charge of stealing. The Police Prosecutor, Insp. Samad Aliu, told… In "News"